social_posts.post_text: Would you spend $1000 on dinner for 2? I live for experiences! I’ll take vacations over designer bags any day. This was our experience at @hidenmiami . It was a really cool luxury dining experience at an 8 seat counter restaurant hidden in a back room of a casual taco bar. You need a password to enter, and a lot of luck to get a reservation! We’ve been trying to get in for MONTHS! High-end restaurants are like the equivalent of a golf course. You can meet some really cool decision-makers. The most we’ve ever spent on a dinner for 2 was about $3000. We’ve got some pretty lofty generational wealth goals, so it’s not something we do often right now, but when we do, we go BIG! We’re planning the next @luxcouplevacay to Jamaica!!! I know, I know…you’ve been there. But have you been Lux style?! We’re planning lux dinners and a trip to @mrcheffito’s new endeavor @elevatemobay ! Drop your email for deets when they drop.

London is NOT my broke best friend lol. We hired her at 1-year-old as our social media model earning $6500 per year (the 2023 max allowance). Her earnings go into her Roth IRA and grow federally tax-free. When she’s 21 she’ll take over the account and keep contributing. She’ll have MILLIONS.

The Proverbs 31 woman was able to laugh without fear of the future because she placed her hope in the Lord AND she planned ahead. I’ve spent time and money learning how to set my family up for greatness. Here’s what else we’ve done:

🔑She will be our trust beneficiary and inherit our portfolio of real estate investments, probate-free and capital gains tax-free. Thank you @dcrosby22 for your friendship and mentorship. 😊

🔑She has a custodial brokerage account with multiple investments (dividend and growth stocks).

🔑A college savings plan (I’m personally not a fan of the 529 plan because I don’t know if college will be as relevant in 16 years. If you use it for noneducation-related expenses, you’ll incur a penalty and owe taxes on any investment gains.)

🔑Whole life insurance policy with a cash value (a portion of the premium goes toward building cash value, which can be accessed for any reason. When you buy a policy for a child, a bigger portion of the premium will go toward the cash value because the cost of insurance is low, and there’s more time for the cash value to build.

Screenshot this and learn more about each one if you have kids that you want to set up in life. And make sure you put on your mask first!! Build an emergency fund, save for retirement, and have life insurance for yourself first! 💗

Did you know you can do a day trip to the Bahamas?! My family and I are in Fort Lauderdale for my mom’s birthday and we decided to do a day trip to Bimini Bahamas from Ft. Lauderdale on the @baleariaferry ! Roundtrip adult tickets were $225. Children 2 and under are free and children 3-13 are $156. The day pass to @hilton World Resort Bimini to use their pools and beach club is $40 for 3 and older. The pools are refreshing, and the beach 🤯. It was absolutely amazing!!! Crystal clear waters, white sands, and a great beach restaurant for lunch. Transportation on the tram from the ferry to the Hilton and the beach club is complimentary and only about a 2-5 minute ride. We left the house at 6am and were home by 10pm. 🥰 Would you do a day trip out the country?

We just started our summer programming of @deannarobinsonwellness last week and this rotation of programming just hits a little different. About 3 weeks ago, right before we started our summer program, we lost two of our former participants to gun violence in DC. 💔 

Our program is supported Exodus Treatment Center and the @mayor_bowser Administration to ensure children and youth in the District have access to quality educational and enrichment activities beyond the school day. We have been facilitating programs at multiple sites in Southeast DC year ‘round for about 5 years—even switching to live virtual and video content learning during the pandemic. In addition to nutrition and fitness, our 3rd cornerstone is centered around social-emotional learning. This is especially important now as violence and criminal activity soars in DC, especially amongst youth. Programs like ours that teach students the skills to understand and manage their emotions have been tied to reductions in aggression, declines in school suspensions, suicidal thoughts, and improvements in emotion regulation and academic outcomes.

We have the most amazing team (@llcoolchef @itsrachelashley @theeholisticsol ) who are so passionate about being a part of the solution! ♥️

Thank you to @kitchencray and @mrcheffito for partnering with me to sponsor the repast. With the help of @llcoolchef we made it happen with a day’s notice. 🙏🏾 It’s such a blessing to be a blessing. ✨

This week wrapped up our @deannarobinsonwellness summer camp programming in SE Washington DC. We have been running our program in ward 7 and 8 for about 5 years now, but the past year has really been eye-opening as to the impact that programs like ours have. Our youth are experiencing exponentially rising community violence (among their peers) and many other Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACEs).

on a lighter note, we had so much fun, learning and developing with our students this week! We role played and implemented some of the social-emotional learning (SEL) tools we learned over the six weeks like kindness, confidence, patience, calmness and sportsmanship. We were honored to have a few special guest chefs, join us for a mystery basket cooking competition. Thank you so much @mrcheffito @chefstretch and @mental_mayhem. We were also able to have students participate in a ‘farm to table’ experience by harvesting the herbs they grew in their urban garden, and using them to prepare a healthy zucchini noodle spaghetti, and a mint infused lemonade. They absolutely loved it, and came back for seconds! 😋 Thank you so much to @llcoolchef and @itsrachelashley for being the absolute best facilitators of our programs.

While we were in St. Maarten this happened to my mom’s house.  By the grace of God (and fire safety preparation) everyone was able to escape and is safe and unharmed. Many people remember my mom’s house because it’s right on a busy corner and my mom cared for so many people and children. 💗

This just so happened to take place during Fire Prevention Week, so I wanted to take a moment to send out this important message. 

🔥Take a few minutes to check the batteries in your smoke alarms. Almost 3 of every 5 home fire deaths resulted from fires with no smoke alarms or no working smoke alarms (NFPA)

🔥Ensure that you have a fire extinguisher in your kitchen that’s not expired. Know how to work it! Remember the acronym PASS.

Pull the pin.
Aim low at the base of the fire.
Squeeze the handle slowly.
Sweep the nozzle side to side.

🔥Unattended cooking is the #1 cause of home fires (NFPA) Be on alert! If you are sleepy or have consumed alcohol or drugs, don’t cook. If you have a small grease cooking fire remember water and oil don’t mix!! On the stovetop, smother the flames by sliding a lid over the pan and turning off the burner. Leave the pan covered until it is completely cooled. For an oven fire, turn off the heat and keep the door closed.

If you live in Prince George’s County MD and you're in need of a free smoke alarm installed in your home, call 301-583-2200. 

Thank you for the brave work you do @pgfd_fire_chief_ and @pgfdnews ♥️

I always say that exercise/fitness is a microcosm of life. It reflects so many life situations/lessons. Since many people have made “exercise” resolutions for 2024, let me share with you a few benefits that you may not have thought about. 💪🏾

🔑In a spin class I took, we warmed up in 18 gear. It was so tough, I didn’t know if I would make it through the class! Fast forward 40 mins into the class: we had the gear set to a grueling 24 for a climb; then we brought it down to an 18 to recover. The same 18 gear from the warm-up felt like a relief! You are growing through experience! Over time you will find that life isn’t necessarily any easier or harder; it’s just that you’ve grown and God has conditioned you.

🔑Sometimes you don’t feel like working out. But all the time the benefit is there. In life sometimes you have to muster up motivation. Commitment is staying true to what you said you would do long after the mood that you said it in has left.

🔑In the fitness world we have this concept of “training to failure”. Basically you train to maximum exertion until your muscles can’t anymore. And this concept is welcomed and positive (when performed safely). It’s great for increasing strength and muscle mass. In life, we can’t be afraid to fail. Many times failure makes us greater. 💗

In 2024…

I pray that you seek God’s face continually through prayer and fasting, worship, and the Word.

We are WHOLE, HEALED, COMPLETE and LACK NOTHING! Even if that’s not your story right now, speak life that it will be.

I’ll be gone seeking God’s face for the next 21 days. Just didn’t want y’all to worry. lol✌🏾
